ltiline mode, but receive no error. The search fails silently.\r\n\r\nN.B. Searching using the PCRE2 engine, with multiline mode (-U) works as expected:\r\n```\r\nrg -PU \"RIP\\nGREP\" corpus.txt\r\n```\r\nOutput:\r\n```\r\n2:RIP\r\n3:GREP\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### If this is a bug, what is the actual behavior?\r\n\r\nSee output above\r\n\r\n#### If this is a bug, what is the expected behavior?\r\n\r\nI would expect ripgrep to throw an error, warning the user that newlines cannot be matched outside multiline mode (-U) when using PCRE2. This would yield the same behaviour as when Rust's engine is used (#1055)","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/BurntSushi/ripgrep/issues/1261/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/BurntSushi/ripgrep/issues/1261/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"}]